<TITLE> DU suspends BCL man </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 19 (bdnews24.com) Dhaka University has suspended BCL activist, currently in jail for possession of a revolver. Mohammad Arif, a Chhatra League activist and final year history student living in Surya Sen Hall, was arrested in possession of a revolver Monday. DU proctor KM Saiful Islam told bdnews24.com: "Arif has been suspended temporarily for eroding the university's image." bdnews24.com on Monday reported that Arif was arrested at Babubazar check-post while he was coming from Keraniganj on a motorcycle. Police stopped him for routine inspection and found a revolver tucked into his waist, Md Rakibul Islam, duty officer of the Kotwali Police Station, told bdnews24.com Monday. bdne
